OL,3,GNorthern Ireland
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FThe day will begin dry with
OL,6,Fbright or sunny spells. Scattered
OL,7,Fshowers will spread east from mid
OL,8,Fmorning but will begin to clear as
OL,9,Fcloud increases towards the evening.
OL,10,
OL,11,CTonight:FThe evening will be cloudy
OL,12,Fwith a few showers, these mostly in
OL,13,Fthe west. Outbreaks of rain soon
OL,14,Fspread north becoming widespread and
OL,15,Fheavy from around midnight.
OL,16,
OL,17,CSaturday:FCloudy with widespread and
OL,18,Fheavy rain at first. This rain will
OL,19,Fclear from the southwest to leave the
OL,20,Farea dry with sunny spells by the
OL,21,Fevening.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
